      <body>
         <pb facs="1876_04_24_Reddelien_Yokohama_von_Konsulat_des_Deutschen_Reichs_Yokohama_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>
            <seg rend="left">
               <hi rend="print">
                  <orgName type="gov" ref="K01078">Konsulat<lb/> des<lb/> Deutschen
                            Reichs</orgName>
                  <lb/> No</hi> 349.</seg>
            <seg rend="right">
               <hi rend="latintype">
                  <placeName ref="K00525">Yokohama</placeName>
               </hi>, den <date when="1876-04-24">24<hi rend="superscript">ten</hi> April
                        1876</date>
            </seg>
            <lb/>
            <lb/> Umstehend behändige ich Ihnen ergebenst Abschrift eines<lb/> von dem hiesigen
                japanischen Gerichtshof in Sachen <hi rend="latintype">
               <orgName type="firm" ref="K01066">Schultze, Reis +Co</orgName>
            </hi>
            <lb/> in Liquidation wider <hi rend="latintype">
               <persName ref="K00060">Hayashi Genyemon</persName>
            </hi> eingegangenen Schreibens,<lb/> sowie gleichzeitig anliegend die in demselben
                erwähnten
                <measure type="currency" unit="yen" quantity="19.613"><hi rend="latintype">19 <term type="currency" ref="K01870">Yen</term> 61 <hi rend="superscript">3</hi>/10 Sen</hi></measure>
            <lb/> mit dem Ersuchen, dem Gerichte die verlangte Empfangsbescheinigung<lb/>
                gefälligst einzusenden.<lb/>
            <seg rend="right">In Verantwortung:<lb/>
               <hi rend="latintype">
                  <persName ref="K00061">Schäffer</persName>
               </hi>
            </seg>
            <lb/>
            <lb/>
            <seg rend="left">An<lb/> Herren <hi rend="latintype">
                  <persName ref="K00029">G. Reddelien</persName>,</hi>
               <lb/> Liquidator der Firma <hi rend="latintype">
                  <orgName type="firm" ref="K01066">Schultze, Reis +Comp.</orgName>
                  <lb/>
                  <unclear reason="illegible">Hier</unclear>
               </hi>
            </seg>
         </p>
         <pb facs="1876_04_24_Reddelien_Yokohama_von_Konsulat_des_Deutschen_Reichs_Yokohama_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1876_04_24_Reddelien_Yokohama_von_Konsulat_des_Deutschen_Reichs_Yokohama_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <p>
            <seg rend="left">
               <hi rend="underline">Translation</hi>
               <lb/>N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
               <hi rend="underline">122</hi>
            </seg>
            <seg rend="right">
               <orgName type="gov" ref="K01079">Judicial Court<lb/>Kanagawa</orgName>
               <lb/>
               <date when="1876-04-11">11<hi rend="underline">th</hi> April 1876</date>
            </seg>
            <lb/> Sir, <lb/> in the Case of <orgName type="firm" ref="K01066">Schultze Reis
                        +C<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
            </orgName> against <persName ref="K00060">Hayashi<lb/> Genyemon</persName> defandant
                having been proceeded with in<lb/> accordance with the bankruptcy law. Enclosed I
                beg<lb/> to forward you the amount of <measure type="currency" unit="yen" quantity="19.613">19 <term type="currency" ref="K01870">Yen</term> 61 sen and 3
                rin</measure><lb/> and request that you hand same over to plaintiffs <lb/> against their
                receipt for this court, with regard to the<lb/> balance still due to be paid by the
                    <unclear>garantor </unclear>(<persName ref="K00062">Hayashi<lb/>
                    Bunzo</persName>), he being unable to do so will also be declared<lb/> a
                bankrupt. and the dividends after proceedings have<lb/> been taken, will be duly
                forwarded to you-<lb/> Requesting that you inform plaintiffs of same-<lb/>
            <seg rend="right"> I have the honour to be,<lb/> Sir, <lb/> Your most obedient <choice>
                  <abbr>Sert.</abbr>
                  <expan>Servant</expan>
               </choice>
               <lb/> (sign) <persName ref="K00063">Asaina Kansui</persName>
               <lb/> for President</seg>
            <lb/>
            <lb/>
            <seg rend="left">
               <persName ref="K00061">Armin Schäffer</persName> Esq<hi rend="superscript">re</hi>
               <lb/> Adj. Consul for the German Empire--</seg>
         </p>
         <pb facs="1876_04_24_Reddelien_Yokohama_von_Konsulat_des_Deutschen_Reichs_Yokohama_4.tif" n="4"/>
      </body>
   </text>
   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1876_04_24_Reddelien_Yokohama_von_Konsulat_des_Deutschen_Reichs_Yokohama_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>Consulate<lb/>of the <lb/>German Empire <lb/> No 349.<lb/> Yokohama, 24th April
                1876<lb/>Overleaf I am delivering to you respectfully a copy of a
                letter<lb/>received from the local Japanese court regarding the case of
                <lb/>Schultze, Reis +Co in liquidation against Hayashi Genyemon<lb/>as well as, at
                the same time, the 19 Yen 61 3/10 Sen, enclosed, that<lb/>are mentioned in the
                letter with the request that you kindly send in<lb/>to the court the requested note
                of receipt. <lb/>By authority of:<lb/>Schäffer<lb/>
            <lb/>To<lb/>Mr. G. Reddelien,<lb/>Liquidator of the firm Schultze, Reis
                +Comp.<lb/>Here[?]</p>
         <pb facs="1876_04_24_Reddelien_Yokohama_von_Konsulat_des_Deutschen_Reichs_Yokohama_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1876_04_24_Reddelien_Yokohama_von_Konsulat_des_Deutschen_Reichs_Yokohama_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1876_04_24_Reddelien_Yokohama_von_Konsulat_des_Deutschen_Reichs_Yokohama_4.tif" n="4"/>
      </body>
   </text>
